[commands]
check_smsd=$USER1$/check_smsd -f /etc/smsd.conf -w $ARG1$ -c $ARG2$

[name]
check_smsd

[info]
This plugin is used to monitor the number of failed sms messages on a op5 Monitor server.

[why]
To give you notifications when there are too many failed sms on your server.

[how]
By checking the number of files in the error directory in your smsd spool directory.

[platforms]
op5 Monitor or any other host running smsd

[categories]
Misc

[support]
4

[tags]
sms, gsm, sms spool queue
